From Rick Miller Subject How to Make Your Own X Face in Easy Steps Will someone who can 'see' the X Face included in this header please reply and tell me if it turned out okay I'm not all too sure about my viewing I hand converted this thing in vi from a Sun what a pain For folks who haven't the slightest it went like this How to Make Your Own X Face in Easy Steps Scan my Drivers' License into a Use WinGIF to 'trim' my face out of the license 'reduce' it by half and convert it to Use Paintbrush to touch up Use WinGIF to 'reduce' it by half Use Paintbrush to touch up Use WinGIF to 'reduce' it by half again and convert it to now over to the UNIX Use Snapshot to convert the to a Sun Use IconEdit to touch it up and convert it to an X Use vi yes a text editor to manually convert the rasterfile into the Uncompressed X Face Lots of global ed commands and by the time you're done you'll mirror hex bytewise in your sleep now over to the Linux Use compface to convert it to what you see here A m Dob BO 'E k G PD vVxCXSn nVHE W X zs O HFU LwzYgH Try viewing it by whatever means you have Go back to step but do it right this Rick Miller Ricxjo Muelisto Send a postcard get one back Enposxtigu bildkarton kaj vi ricevos alion RICK MILLER WOODS MUSKEGO USA